00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:03.970
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, D.C.

00:00:19.430 --> 00:00:21.170
&gt;&gt; David Mao: Good
afternoon everyone.

00:00:21.170 --> 00:00:23.460
Welcome to the Library of Congress.

00:00:23.460 --> 00:00:28.130
Welcome to this celebratory
event for a great day here --

00:00:28.130 --> 00:00:30.800
finally have some nice weather
here in Washington, and I'm so glad

00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:32.960
that it's happening today.

00:00:32.960 --> 00:00:36.840
We are here to celebrate the
winners of the 2015 Library

00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:39.350
of Congress Literacy Awards.

00:00:39.350 --> 00:00:41.540
My name is David Mao and I
have the privilege of serving

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:45.530
as the Acting Librarian of Congress
and again, welcome to the library.

00:00:45.530 --> 00:00:49.120
The Library of Congress
Literacy Awards originated with

00:00:49.120 --> 00:00:53.070
and is sponsored by
philanthropist David Rubenstein.

00:00:53.070 --> 00:00:57.100
The awards -- first
announced in January 2013 --

00:00:57.100 --> 00:00:59.590
helps support organizations
that worked to promote reading

00:00:59.590 --> 00:01:03.210
and literacy in the United
States and around the world.

00:01:03.210 --> 00:01:08.350
The awards highlight and reward
organizations for their exemplary,

00:01:08.350 --> 00:01:11.940
innovative, and easily
replicable work.

00:01:11.940 --> 00:01:15.600
Now these awards, they
benefit not only the winners,

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:18.970
but also new groups,
organizations, and individuals

00:01:18.970 --> 00:01:22.040
through the best practices
of all of our applicants.

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:25.140
And so anywhere around the
world, people can be involved

00:01:25.140 --> 00:01:27.590
in alleviating the
scourge of illiteracy.

00:01:27.590 --> 00:01:31.790
And that's one of the benefits
of all of these awards.

00:01:31.790 --> 00:01:33.130
We're very fortunate to have

00:01:33.130 --> 00:01:37.020
with us today our very generous
benefactor, David Rubenstein.

00:01:37.020 --> 00:01:41.750
He has perfected what he has
called "patriotic philanthropy"

00:01:41.750 --> 00:01:45.230
