00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:07.680
United Through Reading
was founded in 1989

00:26:07.680 --> 00:26:10.920
and began serving the military
during the first Gulf War.

00:26:10.920 --> 00:26:15.090
Our founder, Betty Mohlenbrock, was
the wife of a navy flight surgeon.

00:26:15.090 --> 00:26:18.740
And when he deployed to Vietnam,
their daughter was a year old.

00:26:18.740 --> 00:26:24.510
When he returned, she didn't
recognize him a year later.

00:26:24.510 --> 00:26:25.980
Betty was also a reading teacher

00:26:25.980 --> 00:26:28.230
who saw children starting
school not prepared

00:26:28.230 --> 00:26:30.270
to read and unprepared to learn.

00:26:30.270 --> 00:26:35.530 position:56%
And so these two experiences came
together for her with this bold idea

00:26:35.530 --> 00:26:37.580
that service members
could stay connected

00:26:37.580 --> 00:26:41.430
with each other during
separations through the simple act

00:26:41.430 --> 00:26:43.900
of reading a story book aloud.

00:26:43.900 --> 00:26:47.390
And so, like you said
earlier, it is simple.

00:26:47.390 --> 00:26:51.100
What we do is very simple
but to profound effect.

00:26:51.100 --> 00:26:55.330
Our mission is to unite military
families facing physical separation

00:26:55.330 --> 00:26:57.250
by facilitating the
bonding experience

00:26:57.250 --> 00:26:58.550
of reading aloud together.

00:26:58.550 --> 00:27:02.680
And our vision is that all
children will feel the security

00:27:02.680 --> 00:27:06.430
of caring family relations
and develop a love of reading

00:27:06.430 --> 00:27:08.940
through that read aloud experience.

00:27:10.040 --> 00:27:13.580
As many of you know, military
families face unique challenges.

00:27:13.580 --> 00:27:17.980
Despite incredible bravery,
resilience, and strength,

00:27:17.980 --> 00:27:21.160
military families --
especially the children --

00:27:21.160 --> 00:27:25.180
have increased risk factors or
are associated with frequent moves

00:27:25.180 --> 00:27:28.550
and deployments that
often bring instability

00:27:28.550 --> 00:27:30.650
to our military families.

00:27:30.650 --> 00:27:32.340
Research indicates that children

00:27:32.340 --> 00:27:37.420
from active duty military families
experience significantly higher

00:27:37.420 --> 00:27:41.380
levels of emotional difficulties
during family separations

00:27:41.380 --> 00:27:43.690
than children of the
general population.

00:27:43.690 --> 00:27:45.960
And in a recent study, one-third

00:27:45.960 --> 00:27:50.720
of our military children surveyed
reported symptoms of anxiety.

00:27:50.720 --> 00:27:53.650
Longer deployments are linked
to greater difficulties

00:27:53.650 --> 00:27:57.230
in children's social and
emotional functioning.

00:27:57.230 --> 00:28:01.820
And if that weren't distressing
enough, a recent study

00:28:01.820 --> 00:28:04.910
by the RAND Corporation
found an association

00:28:04.910 --> 00:28:08.210
between military children who
have endured long separations

00:28:08.210 --> 00:28:12.970
from a parent and lower
achievement in reading and math.

00:28:17.100 --> 00:28:20.120
Counterbalancing these findings,
there's good news reported

00:28:20.120 --> 00:28:21.470
by numerous studies that point

00:28:21.470 --> 00:28:24.660
to a very simple thing
to help these children.

00:28:24.660 --> 00:28:26.580
The single most important activity

00:28:26.580 --> 00:28:30.200
for building earliest
emergent reading skills appears

00:28:30.200 --> 00:28:32.410
to be reading aloud to children.

00:28:32.410 --> 00:28:33.710
It's simple.

00:28:33.710 --> 00:28:37.610
And this conclusion is
also at the very heart

00:28:37.610 --> 00:28:39.230
of United Through Reading.

00:28:39.230 --> 00:28:43.810
We use that treasured family
practice of story time

00:28:43.810 --> 00:28:48.280
to sustain healthy family
bonds during separations

00:28:48.280 --> 00:28:50.540
and alleviate the stress
for family members.

00:28:50.540 --> 00:28:54.680
And both are essential to
helping our at-risk children

00:28:54.680 --> 00:28:56.190
in learning to love reading.

