01:11:20.290 --> 01:11:22.240
&gt;&gt; Kyle Zimmer: I didn't say that.

01:11:22.240 --> 01:11:25.080
&gt;&gt; David Rubenstein: So when your
children were learning to read,

01:11:25.080 --> 01:11:27.520
and their teachers were
not doing as good a job

01:11:27.520 --> 01:11:28.920
as you thought they
maybe should have?

01:11:28.920 --> 01:11:30.220
What did you say to the teachers?

01:11:30.220 --> 01:11:31.610
Or you always thought the
teachers were doing a good job?

01:11:31.610 --> 01:11:33.900
&gt;&gt; Kyle Zimmer: I actually always
thought the teachers were doing a

01:11:33.900 --> 01:11:35.200
pretty good job.

01:11:35.200 --> 01:11:40.900
I mean, I think that what we did
at home was we just read a lot.

01:11:40.900 --> 01:11:47.950
And, I think, more important than
the curriculum, in a lot of ways,

01:11:47.950 --> 01:11:51.010
is having fun doing it
and making it something

01:11:51.010 --> 01:11:53.750
that your kids see that you love.

01:11:53.750 --> 01:11:55.950
And they become part of that.

01:11:55.950 --> 01:11:58.770
And that carries a lot.

01:11:58.770 --> 01:12:00.580
&gt;&gt; David Rubenstein: Well, look,
you've done a great job and I want

01:12:00.580 --> 01:12:01.880
to thank you very much

01:12:01.880 --> 01:12:03.180
for everything you've
done for the country --

01:12:03.180 --> 01:12:04.480
&gt;&gt; Kyle Zimmer: Thank you.

01:12:04.480 --> 01:12:05.780
Thank you.

01:12:05.780 --> 01:12:07.080
&gt;&gt; David Rubenstein: And
for the world, eventually.

01:12:07.080 --> 01:12:08.380
&gt;&gt; Kyle Zimmer: Well, thank you.

01:12:08.380 --> 01:12:09.680
&gt;&gt; David Rubenstein:
Starting First Book.

01:12:09.680 --> 01:12:10.980
Thank you very much.

01:12:10.980 --> 01:12:12.280
&gt;&gt; Kyle Zimmer: Thank you
and you know, before --

01:12:12.280 --> 01:12:13.580
[ Applause ]

01:12:13.580 --> 01:12:15.150
Thanks. Before we break,
I just want to say,

01:12:15.150 --> 01:12:19.310
the Lincoln Memorial is
my favorite memorial.

01:12:19.310 --> 01:12:21.820
And on behalf of everyone
in Washington,

01:12:21.820 --> 01:12:23.240
and everyone in the country --

01:12:23.240 --> 01:12:24.540
&gt;&gt; David Rubenstein:
Thank you very much.

01:12:24.540 --> 01:12:26.510
&gt;&gt; Kyle Zimmer: Thank you so
much for stepping up on that.

01:12:26.510 --> 01:12:39.200
[ Applause ]

01:12:39.200 --> 01:12:41.130
&gt;&gt; David Mao: Thank you so much
for sharing those words with us.

01:12:41.130 --> 01:12:44.920
And let's join again and thank
David for sponsoring the Library

01:12:44.920 --> 01:12:46.720
of Congress Literacy Awards.

01:12:46.720 --> 01:12:51.040
[ Applause ]

01:12:51.040 --> 01:12:52.930
Congratulations again
to award winners.

01:12:52.930 --> 01:12:55.080
Thank you to our advisory
board members here.

01:12:55.080 --> 01:12:58.400
Actually, thank you to all of
you because it's working together

01:12:58.400 --> 01:13:02.190
that we can help with this
problem that we have in the world

01:13:02.190 --> 01:13:05.340
and that is fighting illiteracy.

